  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mobilising local resources for succour to the less privileged.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The low access to education, loss of livelihood, lack of infrastructures, health facilities and stringent poverty situations in some parts of Nigeria brought about by the natural disasters and conflict especially in the north east need to be addressed. These gaps were identified during the nutrition and education in Emergency needs assessment Caritas Nigeria conducted through our local implementing partners (JDPCs). Support to the most vulnerable especially those affected by natural and man-made disasters will be more sustainable with as there will be continuous support through the ownership of Caritas Nigeria by Nigerians.</narrative>
  </description>
